en: Florence 4209
beazley_number
collection_history

Excavated by the painter Alessandro Franois from around a tomb at Chiusi. The vase had been broken in antiquity and scattered over a wide area; between 1844 and 1845 Franois is said to have excavated an area the size of the Coliseum looking for further fragments of the vase.
